Author: damnitjanet6
Text: No I get you completely! It’s normally manageable, but then whenever I drive past that building I get super anxious and uncomfortable, and I guess going in there yesterday was just tooo much for my little brain to handle and I completely short-circuited.

Author: IDKijustdrinkhere
Text: This is how I feel about the town I grew up in. It’s like the second I cross the line into said town, I’m in a thick fog of depression. I had to drive there for a work thing yesterday and just could not wait to leave. I’ve tried to explain the feeling to my sisters (they grew up there too) and they look at me like I am crazy. So, guess it’s just me who had a depressing childhood haha. 🤷🏻‍♀️
